                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1307">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GGW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guthrie</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of April 17, midnight. The Department shares sentiment of <persName
                        corresp="#p_SBY1">Baron Sakatani</persName> opposing proposed economic
                    alliance. You may say Department would regret any combination which might
                    restrict commerce between Japan and United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
